----------
README
----------

This file contains information on how to use the sanskrit wordnet database downloaded from Sanskrit WordNet Website (http://www.cfilt.iitb.ac.in/wordnet/webswn/).

Step 1: You will need MySQL to use this database. Please install MySQL on your system. We do not support any other format currently.
Step 2: Create an empty database named 'sanskrit_wordnet' in MySQL using "CREATE DATABASE sanskrit_wordnet".
Step 3: To import the database, you can enter the command:

mysql -u<username> -p<password> sanskrit_wordnet < sanskrit.sql

OR
 
you can use PHPMyAdmin to import the database into MySQL, or any other compatible data import tools available on the internet.

This imports the table 'synset_data' in sanskrit_wordnet database.

For any other queries:
Please contact Diptesh Kanojia at dipteshkanojia [at] gmail [dot] com
